Sentencas: Sr2-xNaxFeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-delta is synthesized as an anode material for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Enhanced activity and stability of Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ anode for solid oxide fuel cells with Na doping

Sentencas: The effects of Na on the crystalline phase and electrical properties are investigated.
Titulo: Enhanced activity and stability of Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ anode for solid oxide fuel cells with Na doping

Sentencas: The main perovskite phase changes into a Ruddlesden-Popper structure after reduction when xis less than 0.1, while the material with a higher amount of Na keeps the perovskite structure.
Titulo: Enhanced activity and stability of Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ anode for solid oxide fuel cells with Na doping

Sentencas: FeNix alloy nanoparticles are exsolved during reduction, in which the content of Ni increases with the rise of Na amount.
Titulo: Enhanced activity and stability of Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ anode for solid oxide fuel cells with Na doping

Sentencas: The surface oxygen vacancy concentration is also influenced by the doping of Na, and the highest value is reached when x is 0.1.
Titulo: Enhanced activity and stability of Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ anode for solid oxide fuel cells with Na doping

Sentencas: Sr1.9Na0.1FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-delta anode exhibits the highest activity, and a single cell supported by a 300-mu m-thick La0.8S0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta electrolyte layer shows maximum power densities of 1495 and 627 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C with H-2 and wet CH4 as fuels, respectively.
Titulo: Enhanced activity and stability of Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ anode for solid oxide fuel cells with Na doping

Sentencas: The coking resistance of the anode is also improved with Na doping.
Titulo: Enhanced activity and stability of Sr2FeMo0.65Ni0.35O6-δ anode for solid oxide fuel cells with Na doping
